==Indonesian==
===Noun===
'''abang'''
# elder [[brother]]

===Usage note===
''abang/bang'' as a form of address: [[you]] (used to address an elder brother or cousin, a male friend (who is older than oneself is), a husband or boy-friend).  Sometimes it is used with a name (Bang Samsul, Bang Amir, ...).

===Examples===
'''Bang''' Erwin, [[mau]] [[ke]] [[mana]]?
* Erwin, where are you going?

[[Nanti]] [[malam]] [[aku]] [[ke]] [[rumah]] '''Abang'''.
* I'll come to your house tonight/this evening.

